  "texts": [
    "As DPG, NSG, and SSG rely on KGraph and EFANNA, they were also excluded from larger datasets.",
    "Indexing Time.",
    "Figure 7 demonstrates that II-based approaches have the lowest indexing time across dataset sizes.",
    "In particular, the II and DC-based approach ELPIS, is 2.7x faster than HNSW and 4x faster than NSG for both 1M and 25GB dataset sizes, while HNSW is 1.4x faster than NGT.",
    "Note that NSG's indexing time includes both the construction of its base graph, EFANNA, which is time-intensive, and the refinement with NSG."
  ],
